    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="993"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d993">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.623/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-05T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 5, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>277. Reference Department’s instruction 313, August 26. In a note dated December
                    4 Minister for Foreign Affairs gives approval to proposal of Smithsonian
                    Institution for the establishment of a research laboratory on the Galápagos
                    Islands. The Ecuadoran Government requests in addition that a small
                    meteorological station be made a part of the laboratory.</p>
                <p>Text of the note<note n="35" xml:id="d993fn1">Not printed.</note> will be
                    forwarded in air mail pouch leaving here December 7.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
